<ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">People</ENAMEX> are what make internal control work. The responsibility
for good internal control rests with all <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">managers</ENAMEX>. <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">Management</ENAMEX> sets
the objectives, puts the control mechanisms and activities in
place, and <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">monitors</ENAMEX> and evaluates the control. However, all
